<div type="description" n="monument">
<head>Description of Monument</head>

<p>Rectangular <rs type="material" key="marmor">white marble</rs> <rs type="objectType"><rs type="objectType">statue base</rs> shaft</rs>, with moulded panels on all four sides in two large joining fragments (together <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="width">0.49</measure>  × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">1.125</measure>  × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="depth">0.49</measure>) and one small fragment of ll. 14-16 (<measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="width">0.165</measure>  × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.21</measure>  × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="depth">0.10</measure>);</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="text">
<head>Description of Text</head>
<p> Inscribed on two adjacent faces. Face a, to the left, has broken moulding, and is broken down the left side. Face b is pitted to receive plaster. The moulding on face a survives at the upper edge; the text must therefore have begun on an upper feature. Traces of the plaster which covered the inscriptions when the stone was re-used are still adhering.</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="letters">
<head>Letters</head>
<p>Face a: <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.02</measure>; ligatured <foreign lang="grc">ΝΤ</foreign> l.14, <foreign lang="grc">ΗΜ</foreign> l.15, <foreign lang="grc">ΝΗ</foreign> l.22, 23, <foreign lang="grc">ΤΕ</foreign> l.23. Apex on <foreign lang="grc">ΥΙ</foreign>, l.5. Circular stops. Face b: <measure dim="height" type="length" unit="metre">0.025</measure>; <foreign lang="grc">Π</foreign> with a vertical line through the cross-bar, presumably <foreign lang="grc">ΠΙ</foreign> in ligature, line 3.</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="date">
<head>Date</head>
<p><date notBefore="0101" notAfter="0300" exact="none">Second to third centuries A.D.</date> (<rs type="criteria">lettering</rs>, <rs type="criteria">prosopography</rs>).</p>
</div>
